ve%20upsides%20from%20rare%20events.%20His%20contrarian%20approach%20allowed%20him%20to%20rake%20in%20gains%20during%20the%201987%20crash%2C%20when%20he%20had%20positions%20in%20cheap%20Eurodollar%20options%20that%20benefited%20from%20volatility.%20When%20the%20tides%20turned%2C%20he%20was%20flipping%20%242%20to%20%243%20contracts%20for%20%24300%20to%20%24500%2C%20Patterson%20wrote.%20In%201998%2C%20it%20happened%20again%20after%20Russia%20defaulted%20on%20its%20debt%2C%20causing%20a%20stock%20market%20meltdown.%20Taleb%20made%20money%20on%20put%20options%20he%20bought%20on%20Russian%20banks%2C%20the%20book%20noted.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBy%202007%2C%20he%20had%20enough%20experience%20under%20his%20belt%20to%20publish%20the%20book%2C%20%26quot%3BThe%20Black%20Swan%2C%26quot%3B%20where%20he%20popularized%20the%20term%20as%20a%20representation%20of%20rare%2C%20unpredictable%20events%20that%20could%20have%20huge%20impacts%2C%20such%20as%209%2F11.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFrom%20that%2C%20a%20way%20to%20measure%20unpredictability%20was%20born%20that%20included%20gray%20swan%20events%3A%20rare%20but%20predictable%20events%20like%20the%202008%20financial%20crisis%20that%20showed%20signs%20of%20trouble%20through%20the%20housing%20bubble.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThen%20there%20are%20fat-tailed%20events%20that%2C%20in%20most%20instances%2C%20have%20normal%20outcomes%2C%20and%20you%20don't%20expect%20to%20have%20huge%20impacts%20on%20markets.%20But%2C%20in%20one%20or%20a%20handful%20of%20data%20points%2C%20the%20outcome%20can%20be%20so%20extreme%20they%20skew%20the%20model.%20While%20Taleb%20didn't%20coin%20it%2C%20he%20helped%20further%20popularize%20it.%20Here%2C%20a%20pandemic%20is%20an%20example%20of%20both%20a%20gray%20and%20fat-tailed%20event%20because%20their%20outcomes%20can%20be%20tracked%2C%20while%20some%20can%20remain%20local%2C%20like%20ebola%2C%20or%20spread%20rapidly%2C%20like%20COVID.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22a4df31ed-faa5-4086-954f-d3a06f7787af%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EBetting%20on%20unpredictability%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWe're%20familiar%20with%20the%20term%20%26quot%3Bdon't%20panic.%26quot%3B%20It's%20probably%20advice%20you%20received%20at%20some%20point%20when%20things%20were%20going%20off%20the%20edge.%20For%20Taleb%2C%20if%20you're%20going%20to%20panic%2C%20do%20it%20early.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20the%20coronavirus%20hit%2C%20that's%20what%20he%20did.%20According%20to%20Patterson's%20book%2C%20the%20alarming%20rate%20of%20contagion%2C%20coupled%20with%20an%20interconnected%20planet%20where%20global%20travel%20was%20constant%2C%20made%20him%20conclude%20that%20this%20could%20get%20very%20big%2C%20very%20fast.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETaleb%20and%20a%20team%20of%20others%20published%20a%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fnecsi.edu%2Fsystemic-risk-of-pandemic-via-novel-pathogens-coronavirus-a-note%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%20note%20on%20January%2026%3C%2Fa%3E%20categorizing%20the%20outbreak%20as%20an%20extreme%20fat-tailed%20event%20that%20could%20have%20the%20risk%20of%20ruin%20because%20of%20its%20non-linear%20spread.%20It%20was%20almost%20three%20months%20before%20the%20US%20declared%20a%20national%20emergency%20on%20March%2013%20and%20before%20the%20stock%20market%20crashed%20on%20March%2020.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUniversa%20Investments%2C%20a%20hedge%20fund%20where%20Taleb%20is%20a%20distinguished%20scientific%20advisor%2C%20posted%20a%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmarkets.businessinsider.com%2Fnews%2Fstocks%2Fblack-swan-fund-universa-investments-4000-percent-return-hedging-coronavirus-2020-4-1029076165%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%204%2C144%25%20return%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20the%20crash%20of%202020.%20A%20bystander%20could%20easily%20assume%20that%20the%20fund%2C%20which%20specializes%20in%20profiting%20from%20market%20shocks%2C%20turned%20certain%20positions%20on%20in%20response%20to%20the%20mounting%20fears.%20But%20that%20was%20far%20from%20the%20case.%20Instead%2C%20the%20firm's%20flagship%20tail-risk%20hedging%20strategy%20continually%20purchases%20daily%20put%20options%20that%20could%20rake%20in%20gains%20in%20the%20event%20of%20a%20crash.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBrandon%20Yarckin%2C%20COO%20of%20Universa%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider%20that%20as%20Taleb%20drafts%20his%20academic%20work%20around%20events%20that%20don't%20directly%20apply%20to%20finance%2C%20such%20as%20Covid%2C%20there%20are%20corollaries%20to%20that%20thought%20process%20that%20help%20the%20investment%20firm%20build%20portfolios.%20Understanding%20the%20interconnectedness%20and%20how%20systems%20behave%20in%20relation%20to%20how%20markets%20behave%20is%20key%20to%20that%20process%2C%20he%20said.%20In%20the%20example%20of%20a%20pandemic%2C%20he%20noted%20that%20there%20are%20similarities%20between%20how%20diseases%20spread%20and%20how%20markets%20crash.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2299fc0009-0feb-4026-a474-a6f869703ff3%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EUS%20deficit%20and%20the%20dollar%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EDuring%20the%20Thursday%20evening%20talk%2C%20Taleb%20addressed%20the%20US%20deficit%20and%20mounting%20debt%2C%20both%20of%20which%20swelled%20after%20the%20pandemic.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20highlighted%20the%20four%20categories%20of%20debt-based%20countries%3A%20those%20with%20low%20growth%20and%20high%20or%20low%20debt%2C%20and%20those%20with%20high%20growth%20and%20high%20or%20low%20debt.%20The%20US%20is%20in%20the%20category%20of%20low%20growth%20and%20high%20debt.%20The%20issue%2C%20he%20said%2C%20is%20that%20debt%20isn't%20made%20for%20large%20mature%20economies%2C%20which%20is%20where%20it's%20usually%20found%20most.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20is%20because%20the%20growth%20trajectory%20tends%20to%20follow%20the%20S-curve%20pattern%3A%20slow%2C%20then%20rapid%2C%20then%20leveling%20off.%20You%20don't%20need%20to%20continue%20growing%20once%20you're%20on%20top%20of%20the%20curve.%20However%2C%20if%20a%20country%20accumulates%20high%20debt%2C%20then%20continued%20growth%20is%20required%20to%20absorb%20it%2C%20he%20noted.%20The%20outcome%20is%20a%20fragile%20leveraged%20financial%20system%20with%20increased%20interconnected%20risk%2C%20which%20is%20the%20US'%20current%20predicament%2C%20he%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETaleb%20emphasized%20that%20government%20expenditures%20aren't%20purely%20to%20blame.%20The%20US%20is%20stuck%20with%20accumulating%20debt-servicing%20costs%2C%20and%20it's%20now%20spending%20more%20on%20interest%20payments%20than%20military%20spending.%20This%20is%20creating%20a%20snowball%20effect%2C%20where%20it%20must%20keep%20borrowing%20the%20difference.%20At%20present%2C%20Taleb%20doesn't%20believe%20that%20the%20ballooning%20debt%20could%20be%20solved%20politically%20or%20by%20increased%20demand%20for%20US%20bonds.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMark%20Spitznagel%2C%20Universa's%20founder%20and%20CIO%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbiggest-stock-market-crash-since-1929-coming-mark-spitznagel-interview-2024-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epreviously%20told%20Business%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20the%20mounting%20credit%20bubble%20could%20lead%20to%20a%20massive%20stock%20market%20crash%20that%20could%20be%20worse%20than%201929.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20for%20the%20US%20dollar%2C%20for%20the%20most%20part%2C%20people%20like%20to%20transact%20with%20it%20because%20it's%20a%20stable%20currency%2C%20Taleb%20said.%20The%20real%20question%20is%20whether%20they%20use%20it%20as%20a%20store%20of%20value.%20Here%2C%20Taleb%20believes%2C%20is%20where%20the%20problem%20lies.%20The%20big%20question%20he%20asked%20the%20audience%20is%2C%20%26quot%3BHow%20safe%20do%20you%20feel%20putting%20your%20money%20in%20Western%20banks%3F%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFrom%20his%20perspective%2C%20not%20very%20safe.%20Since%202022%2C%20the%20financial%20and%20monetary%20systems%20have%20been%20used%20as%20a%20foreign%20policy%20tool%2C%20he%20said.%20Bank%20accounts%20and%20assets%20of%20Russian%20subjects%20have%20been%20frozen%20based%20on%20their%20political%20ties.%20Taleb%20believes%20that%20this%20type%20of%20behavior%20harms%20the%20US%20dollar%20long-term.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fstock-market-risk-debt-dollar-godfather-black-swan-nassim-taleb-2024-10%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1727875297000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66fc82919e0c5c2eeee9e69e%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fstock-market-risk-debt-dollar-godfather-black-swan-nassim-taleb-2024-10%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22For%20Taleb%2C%20if%20you're%20going%20to%20panic%2C%20do%20it%20early.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22lmaidan%40businessinsider.com%20(Laila%20Maidan)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A3%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fstock-market-risk-debt-dollar-godfather-black-swan-nassim-taleb-2024-10%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Parents%20are%20turning%20to%20a%20'paid%20village'%20to%20handle%20childcare%20and%20cleaning.%20Costs%20range%20from%20%24500%20to%20%242%2C600%20a%20month.%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222667%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Teacher%20Keshawna%20Edwards%20zips%20up%20the%20coat%20of%20Montana%20Mason%2C%203%2C%20before%20recess%20at%20Little%20Flowers%20Early%20Childhood%20and%20Development%20Center%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66fc5edb5ccfc192a5525e0d%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EParents%20in%20the%20US%20are%20paying%20from%20%24500%20to%20%242%2C600%20for%20child%20care.%3Cp%3EThe%20Washington%20Post%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3ESix%20moms%20say%20they%20spend%20%24500%20to%20%242%2C600%20monthly%20to%20create%20their%20paid%20villages.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EChildcare%20is%20the%20most%20substantial%20cost%2C%20while%20many%20also%20hire%20cleaners.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThey%20say%20paying%20for%20help%20is%20a%20necessity%20when%20both%20parents%20work.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EAmy%20Johnson%2C%20a%20mom%20of%20two%20in%20Cleveland%2C%20can%20count%20on%20her%20mother%20and%20mother-in-law%20to%20help%20with%20the%20kids%20and%20domestic%20chores%20every%20month.%20Despite%20that%20unpaid%20support%2C%20Johnson%20and%20her%20husband%20pay%20%242%2C600%20a%20month%20for%20childcare%20and%20cleaning%20%E2%80%94%20the%20sort%20of%20paid%20village%20Johnson%20says%20is%20essential%20when%20both%20parents%20are%20working.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BLife%20is%20currently%20a%20juggle%20between%20time%20and%20money%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Johnson%2C%20whose%20kids%20are%202%20and%203.%20Johnson%20and%20her%20husband%20work%20full-time%2C%20and%20Johnson%20also%20runs%20a%20website%2C%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Famybabys.com%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%20Amy%20Baby%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20feel%20if%20we%20don't%20use%20the%20time%20wisely%20to%20create%20more%20revenue%20streams%2C%20we're%20just%20going%20to%20sink%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20told%20BI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EParents%20around%20the%20country%20are%20struggling%20to%20pay%20for%20childcare%20costs%20%E2%80%94%20which%20are%20often%20higher%20than%20a%20mortgage%20or%20rent.%20%3Cspan%3EIn%202018%20(the%20most%20recent%20year%20for%20which%20data%20is%20available)%2C%20median%20childcare%20costs%20ranged%20from%20%244%2C800%20in%20small%20counties%20for%20a%20school-age%20kid%20at%20home%20to%20%2415%2C400%20for%20an%20infant%20at%20a%20center%2C%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fblog.dol.gov%2F2023%2F01%2F24%2Fnew-childcare-data-shows-prices-are-untenable-for-families%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Eaccording%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20to%20the%20Department%20of%20Labor.%20Adjusted%20for%20inflation%2C%20that%20was%20%245%2C000%20to%20%2417%2C000%20in%202022%20m