%20the%20early%202000s%2C%20told%20BI%20that%20the%20move%20aligns%20with%20its%20leadership%20principles.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ERossman%20said%20the%20mandate%20is%20part%20of%20Amazon's%20plan%20to%20%26quot%3Bjump-start%20growth%20again.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20as-told-to%20essay%20is%20based%20on%20a%20conversation%20with%20John%20Rossman%2C%20an%20early%20Amazon%20executive%2C%20business%20strategist%2C%20and%20author%20of%20%26quot%3BThe%20Amazon%20Way.%26quot%3B%20Business%20Insider%20has%20verified%20his%20identity%20and%20employment.%20The%20following%20has%20been%20edited%20for%20length%20and%20clarity.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20was%20an%20early%20Amazon%20leader%20and%20had%20two%20primary%20roles%20from%202002%20to%20late%202005.%20First%2C%20I%20was%20a%20director%20of%20merchant%20integration%20and%20a%20key%20leader%20in%20launching%20the%20marketplace%20business.%20Then%2C%20I%20was%20a%20director%20of%20enterprise%20services%20and%20ran%20all%20of%20Amazon's%20big%20relationships%20with%20large%20e-commerce%20retailers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20a%20very%20formative%20time%20at%20Amazon%20back%20then%2C%20as%20we%20were%20thinking%20through%20Amazon's%20business%20model%20and%20operating%20standpoint%20and%20hammering%20out%20the%20company's%20principles.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEven%20though%20it's%20been%20almost%2020%20years%20since%20I%20left%20Amazon%2C%20the%20way%20they%20think%20about%20things%20and%20operate%20is%20fundamentally%20the%20same%20at%20its%20core%2C%20even%20though%20it's%20much%20larger%20in%20size.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDuring%20my%20time%20there%2C%20there%20was%20no%20position%20on%20remote%20working.%20If%20you%20needed%20to%20collaborate%2C%20it%20was%20through%20conference%20calls%3B%20there%20was%20nothing%20like%20Zoom%20or%20video%20technology.%20Remote%20working%20wasn't%20in%20the%20lexicon%20of%20corporate%20America.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2284aae256-77c8-4f53-b683-1db21216cfd5%5C%22%3EAndy%20Jassy%20is%20thinking%20long-term%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20recent%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famazon-rto-faq-document-spells-out-new-rule-2024-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ereturn-to-office%20mandate%3C%2Fa%3E%20requiring%20employees%20to%20work%20from%20the%20office%20five%20days%20a%20week%20is%20tricky.%20I%20have%20a%20ton%20of%20empathy%20for%20people%20who%20moved%20away%20from%20the%20office%20with%20the%20understanding%20that%20they'd%20be%20able%20to%20work%20remotely%2C%20and%20now%20they%20might%20need%20to%20move%20back.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%20But%20there's%20a%20flip%20side%20to%20this%2C%20and%20that's%20Andy%20Jassy's%20job%20as%20CEO%2C%20which%20is%20to%20create%20a%20company%20that%20is%20still%20vibrant%20and%20growing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20think%20Jassy%20is%20thinking%20long-term%2C%20which%20is%20one%20of%20the%20core%20features%20of%20Amazon's%20leadership%20principles%3A%20long-term%20thinking.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELike%20other%20corporate%20leaders%2C%20he%20seems%20to%20be%20thinking%20that%20he%20needs%20to%20reclaim%20his%20teams'%20energy%20and%20intensity%20and%20sees%20the%20need%20to%20be%20scrappier%2C%20more%20effective%2C%20and%20get%20more%20done%20with%20fewer%20resources.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%228f9a5a8c-a64f-4201-b369-24a74023f9fe%5C%22%3EAmazon%20shouldn't%20apologize%20for%20being%20a%20demanding%20workplace%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20of%20the%20mistakes%20leaders%20make%20about%20culture%20is%20thinking%20that%20culture%20is%20about%20making%20a%20place%20the%20right%20place%20for%20everyone.%20I%20think%20Amazon%20has%20never%20apologized%2C%20and%20they%20shouldn't%20apologize%20for%20being%20a%20demanding%20place%20to%20work%20because%20it%20is%20a%20great%20place%20to%20work%20if%20you%20want%20to%20be%20a%20builder%20and%20get%20things%20done.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20you%20want%20to%20operate%20like%20an%20entrepreneur%20within%20a%20big%20company%2C%20Amazon%20is%20a%20great%20place%2C%20but%20it%20is%20not%20the%20right%20place%20for%20people%20who%20just%20want%20a%20steady%20or%20easier%20situation.%20So%20the%20return-to-office%20push%20is%20Jassy%20saying%20that%20this%20is%20what%20Amazon%20is%2C%20and%20it%20needed%20to%20be%20authentic%20to%20its%20mission%20and%20try%20to%20maintain%20an%20incredible%20brand%20and%20platform.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJassy's%20decision%20to%20stop%20having%20%26quot%3Bpre-meetings%20for%20the%20pre-meetings%20for%20the%20decision%20meetings%26quot%3B%20is%20more%20about%20effectiveness%2C%20urgency%2C%20ownership%2C%20and%20letting%20great%20people%20make%20direct%20decisions%20versus%20all%20these%20layers%20of%20meetings.%20It's%20allowing%20people%20to%20meet%2C%20make%20a%20decision%2C%20and%20move%20on%2C%20making%20Amazon%20a%20quick-moving%20organization.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22859c009d-152d-44b3-9700-67ef91661ee8%5C%22%3EJeff%20Bezos%20disliked%20bureaucracy%20%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EReally%20good%20people%20hate%20working%20in%20a%20bureaucratic%20organization.%20I%20believe%20that%20Jeff%20Bezos%20always%20thought%20that%20bureaucracy%20was%20the%20real%20enemy%20of%20Amazon%2C%20and%20that's%20why%20it's%20important%20for%20the%20company%20to%20be%20lean.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20past%20few%20years%2C%20Amazon's%20annual%20revenue%20growth%20rate%20has%20slowed.%20In%202022%2C%20it%20amounted%20to%209.4%25%2C%20and%2012%25%20in%202023.%20I%20think%20they%20hate%20that%20growth%20percentage%20and%20believe%20growth%20is%20the%20outcome%20of%20creating%20an%20entrepreneurial%20and%20fast-moving%20organization%2C%20so%20Jassy%20is%20likely%20trying%20to%20jump-start%20growth%20again%20through%20all%20these%20different%20moves.%20He's%20focusing%20on%20culture%20and%20the%20operating%20model%20because%20that's%20essential%20to%20getting%20the%20outputs%20that%20you%20want.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20think%20a%20team%20that%20works%20together%20tends%20to%20get%20things%20done%20faster%20and%20can%20be%20more%20efficient.%20So%20Jassy%20probably%20recognizes%20that%2C%20and%20he%20is%20pulling%20all%20the%20levers%20to%20recreate%20a%20great%20place%20to%20be%20a%20builder%20and%20operator.%20That%20was%20what%20Amazon%20was%20like%20in%20the%20early%20days%3B%20you%20had%20the%20ability%20and%20accountability%20to%20get%20hard%20things%20done%2C%20which%20is%20at%20the%20core%20of%20its%20leadership%20principles.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThese%20principles%20are%20not%20empty%20calorie%20mission%20statements%20that%20most%20companies%20have.%20The%20leadership%20principle%20of%20ownership%20is%20relevant%20to%20what's%20happening%20because%20owners%20think%20long-term%20and%20don't%20sacrifice%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Elong-term%20value%20for%20short-term%20results.%20They%20act%20on%20behalf%20of%20the%20entire%20company%20and%20not%20beyond%20just%20their%20own%20team.%20I%20think%20that%20is%20how%20Jassy%20is%20approaching%20this%3B%20he%20has%20to%20act%20like%20an%20owner%20and%20be%20brave%20enough%20to%20do%20something%20that%20he%20knows%20is%20going%20to%20be%20unpopular%20with%20a%20certain%20set%20of%20employees.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22281414b5-8ddc-42b8-b5d3-3d5acb3ad702%5C%22%3EMore%20people%20in%20the%20office%20will%20raise%20standards%20%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20second%20principle%20related%20to%20this%20is%20insisting%20on%20the%20highest%20standards.%20Leaders%20have%20relentlessly%20high%20standards%2C%20and%20I%20think%20Jassy%20is%20getting%20back%20to%20having%20unreasonably%20high%20standards.%20I%20think%20the%20way%20he%20gets%20there%20is%20by%20having%20people%20be%20in%20the%20office%20more.%20Working%20together%20in%20person%20can%20help%20with%20problem-solving%20and%20mentoring%2C%20and%20it's%20hard%20to%20replicate%20that%20whiteboard%20experience%20when%20you're%20at%20home.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20third%20leadership%20principle%20I%20think%20Jassy%20is%20enforcing%20is%20frugality.%20It's%20about%20accomplishing%20more%20with%20less.%20Constraints%20breed%20resourcefulness%2C%20self-sufficiency%2C%20and%20innovation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20last%20principle%20is%20to%20strive%20to%20be%20the%20Earth's%20best%20employer.%20Some%20say%20that%20the%20return-to-office%20policy%20doesn't%20align%20with%20this%20principle%2C%20but%20I%20say%20the%20contrary.%20The%20principle%20says%20that%20leaders%20work%20daily%20to%20create%20a%20safer%2C%20more%20productive%2C%20higher-performing%2C%20and%20diverse%20work%20environment.%20I%20think%20Jassy%20looks%20at%20this%20and%20says%2C%20%26quot%3BThat%20is%20what%20I%20am%20doing.%26quot%3B%20All%20these%20moves%20come%20from%20a%20core%2C%20long-held%20set%20of%20beliefs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20think%20Amazon%20lost%20some%20control%20of%20its%20culture%20in%20the%20pandemic%20when%20it%20got%20big%20too%20quickly%2C%20so%20now%20Jassy%20and%20other%20corporate%20leaders%20are%20trying%20to%20evaluate%20how%20to%20reclaim%20a%20team%20that%20wants%20to%20win%20%E2%80%94%20and%20that's%20what%20a%20championship%20team%20is%20about.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famazon-office-five-days-rto-exec-andy-jassy-2024-10%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1727871900000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66fd20117de5c8fd48348d1b%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famazon-office-five-days-rto-exec-andy-jassy-2024-10%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Amazon's%20five%20day%20return-to-office%20mandate%20aligns%20with%20its%20leadership%20principles%2C%20according%20to%20former%20exec%20John%20Rossman.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22jmann%40insider.com%20(Jyoti%20Mann)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A39%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famazon-office-five-days-rto-exec-andy-jassy-2024-10%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Ad